02005%2C%20the%20company%20was%20acquired%20by%20eBay%20for%20%242.5%20billion.%20In%202009%2C%20a%20portion%20of%20Skype%20was%20resold%20to%20Silver%20Lake%2C%20Andreessen%20Horowitz%2C%20and%20the%20Canadian%20Pension%20Plan%20Investment%20Board%20for%20%241.9%20billion%2C%20giving%20the%20company%20a%20market%20valuation%20of%20%242.75%20billion.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMicrosoft%20acquired%20Skype%20in%202011%20for%20%248.5%20billion%2C%20making%20it%20a%20division%20of%20Microsoft%20with%20its%20former%20CEO%20Tony%20Bates%20reporting%20to%20then-%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-ceo%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMicrosoft%20CEO%3C%2Fa%3E%20Steve%20Ballmer.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20acquisition%2C%20Microsoft%20integrated%20Skype%20into%20its%20product%20lineup%2C%20discontinuing%20Windows%20Messenger%20in%20favor%20of%20the%20Skype%20client%2C%20which%20became%20the%20default%20messaging%20service%20in%20Windows%208.1.%20By%202013%2C%20Skype%20was%20available%20across%20multiple%20platforms%2C%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-windows-pc-vs-apple-mac-os-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWindows%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20macOS%2C%20iPadOS%2C%20iOS%2C%20Android%2C%20and%20BlackBerry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223238%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Former%20Microsoft%20CEO%20Steve%20Ballmer%20shakes%20hands%20with%20former%20Skype%20CEO%20Tony%20Bates%20in%20front%20of%20a%20backdrop%20featuring%20both%20the%20Microsoft%20and%20Skype%20logos.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6733c08488cea3ba1c2041f2%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222159%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EMicrosoft%20acquired%20Skype%20for%20%248.5%20billion.%3Cp%3EJustin%20Sullivan%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226391c909-0186-4fa5-9cc1-5c8c3fd9e923%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESkype%20was%20once%20a%20telecommunications%20industry%20disruptor%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20offering%20free%20voice%20and%20video%20calls%20between%20Skype%20users%20globally%2C%20it%20effectively%20undercut%20traditional%20telecommunications%20providers%20that%20charged%20hefty%20fees%20for%20international%20calls.%20This%20disruptive%20technology%20approach%20that%20Skype%20took%20paid%20dividends%20in%20terms%20of%20the%20platform's%20immense%20popularity%2C%20especially%20in%20regions%20where%20long-distance%20calling%20was%20prohibitively%20expensive.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20paying%20telecommunications%20companies%20long-distance%20rates%2C%20the%20only%20fee%20you'd%20incur%20would%20be%20the%20internet%20data%20that%20Skype%20used%20for%20your%20audio%20or%20video%20call.%20Skype%20also%20offered%20low%20rates%20for%20calls%20to%20landlines%20and%20cellphones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThrough%20its%20North%20American%20subscription%20plan%2C%20you%20could%20get%202%2C000%20minutes%20of%20calling%20for%20%245.94%2Fmonth%20%E2%80%93%20or%20the%20equivalent%20of%20about%200.297%20cents%20per%20minute%3B%20if%20you%20go%20over%202%2C000%20minutes%2C%20the%20rate%20goes%20to%20%240.35%2Fminute.%20For%20US%20only%20calls%2C%20a%202%2C000%20minute%20plan%20costs%20just%20%242.54%20with%20extra%20time%20costing%20only%20%240.15%2Fminute.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222420819b-6253-48c1-af51-9a2e52ec7adb%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3ESkype's%20advantages%20and%20disadvantages%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20no%20longer%20being%20the%20industry%20leader%20in%20terms%20of%20market%20share%2C%20Skype%20is%20still%20a%20capable%20free%20solution%20for%20video%20and%20audio%20calls.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUnlike%20the%20free%20version%20of%20Zoom%2C%20Skype%20doesn't%20have%20a%2030%20minute%20time%20limit.%20Additionally%2C%20in%202023%20Microsoft%20integrated%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fmicrosoft-bing%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBing%3C%2Fa%3E%20AI%20with%