20that%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20made%20his%20decision%20to%20move%20to%20his%20next%20chapter%2C%20I%20have%20determined%20the%20time%20is%20right%20for%20me%20to%20do%20the%20same%2C%20and%20to%20return%20to%20my%20prior%20professional%20life%20of%20teaching%2C%20research%2C%20and%20public%20policy%20analyses.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20expert%20in%20business%20and%20finance%20law%2C%20she%20was%20a%20tenured%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Toronto.%20She%20did%20stints%20as%20a%20visiting%20lecturer%20at%20Yale%20University%20in%20the%20US%20before%20plunging%20into%20politics%20and%20becoming%20the%20MP%20from%20Oakville%20in%20Ontario%20in%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpeaking%20of%20her%20origin%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BDuring%20my%20first%20campaign%2C%20many%20people%20told%20me%20that%20a%20woman%20of%20Indian%20descent%20would%20not%20get%20elected%20in%20Oakville%2C%20Ontario.%20Yet%2C%20Oakville%20rallied%20behind%20me%20not%20once%20but%20twice%20since%202019%2C%20an%20honour%20that%20I%20will%20hold%20in%20my%20heart%20forever.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20father%2C%20S%20V%20Anand%20was%20the%20son%20of%20a%20freedom%20fighter%20from%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20V%20A%20Sundaram%2C%20and%20her%20mother%20Saroj%20Ram%20was%20from%20Punjab%2C%20and%20both%20were%20doctors%20who%20immigrated%20to%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJoining%20the%20Trudeau%20cabinet%20in%202019%20as%20the%20public%20services%20and%20procurement%20minister%2C%20she%20made%20her%20mark%20ensuring%20Canada%20had%20enough%20medical%20equipment%20and%20vaccines%20during%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202021%2C%20she%20received%20the%20high-profile%20defence%20portfolio%20and%20moved%20in%20a%20cabinet%20reshuffle%20to%20be%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Treasury%20Board%2C%20a%20ministerial-level%20post%2C%20overseeing%20government%20operations%20broadly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20she%20became%20the%20transport%20minister%20and%20added%20the%20internal%20trade%20portfolio.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETaking%20stock%20of%20her%20rapid%20rise%20in%20government%2C%20she%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BBack%20in%202019%2C%20I%20could%20never%20have%20imagined%20that%20such%20work%20would%20mean%20navigating%20supply%20chains%20to%20overcome%20a%20global%20pandemic%2C%20addressing%20sexual%20assault%20in%20the%20Canadian%20Armed%20Forces%2C%20ensuring%20military%20aid%20reached%20Ukraine%2C%20overseeing%20the%20Treasury%20Board%20Secretariat%20or%20reinforcing%20Canada's%20Transportation%20systems.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20popularity%20cratering%2C%20Trudeau%20has%20said%20that%20he%20will%20quit%20when%20a%20new%20Liberal%20Party%20leader%2C%20who%20will%20automatically%20become%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20is%20elected%20under%20the%20supervision%20of%20party%20President%20Sachit%20Mehra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20said%20the%20election%20will%20be%20completed%20by%20March%209%2C%20ahead%20of%20parliament%20resuming%20its%20sessions%20on%20March%2024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOpposition%20parties%20have%20threatened%20an%20immediate%20vote%20of%20non-confidence%2C%20which%20would%20lead%20to%20elections%20sooner%20than%20October%20when%20the%20House%20of%20Commons%20term%20runs%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20Abacus%20poll%20after%20Trudeau's%20announcement%20showed%20the%20opposition%20Conservative%20Party%20with%20a%20massive%2027%20per%20cent%20lead%2C%20with%2047%20per%20cent%20voter%20support%20compared%20to%20the%20Liberal's%2020%20per%20cent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20less%20than%20weeks%20or%20months%20to%20try%20to%20turn%20the%20Liberal%20Party's%20fortunes%20around%2C%20leaders%20are%20reluctant%20to%20take%20on%20the%20mantle%20of%20prime%20ministership%20for%20a%20short%20time%2C%20only%20to%20lead%20the%20party%20to%20almost%20certain%20defeat%20in%20the%20parliamentary%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20President-elect%20Trump's%20threat%20to%20impose%2025%20